summaries.short: Selina preps for a debate with her primary opponents; Mike's wife does a style piece on the Veep.
summaries.full: Selina and the staff prep for her debate with Maddox, Chung, Congressman Owen Pierce, and Joe Thornhill--a major-league baseball manager who has recently entered the race. Dan returns with a rosier outlook; Mike's wife Wendy arrives to do a style piece on Selina, but eyes a bigger story involving Ray.

summaries.short: Selina's staff devise a way to make her seem more folksy; Jonah tries to find a new job.
summaries.full: With Thornhill ahead in the polls, Selina and her staff discuss how to make her more folksy. Jonah, in need of a job, meets with Bill Ericsson, and asks his mom to reach out to his influential uncle Jeff. Selina has an interview with a pretentious journalist named Quincy Carter.

summaries.short: In the U.K., the staff worries about Ray's influence over Selina; Dan's nerves begin to fray as Ben gets news that sends him back to D.C.
summaries.full: In the U.K. for the 100th anniversary of WWI, Selina's staff worries about Ray's growing influence on the Veep. Meanwhile, Dan's nerves begin to fray as Ben gets news that sends him back to D.C. Later, Jonah arrives in London to spy for Team Maddox, and Amy leaks a secret.

summaries.full: At an economic summit in Detroit, Selina's staff and her family are peeved by the presence of her new personal trainer, Ray. Meanwhile, Jonah and Mike negotiate a photo-op with Selina and Maddox. Later, Catherine protects her mom from a protestor, and Selina attends a women's gun show.

summaries.short: Season Four Premiere. It's Selina first major speech as President. Her staff races against time to get it ready.
summaries.full: Season Four Premiere. Twenty-four hours before Selina's first major speech as President, her staff frantically tries to work out how she can say two completely opposite things at the same time. Gary questions his worth; Jonah is put off by the hands-on approach of the new VP's chief of staff; Amy learns that Bill Ericsson, a rival campaign manager, may make a play for her job.

summaries.short: Selina has a secret meeting with an outside strategist, and is invited to General Maddox's country house.
summaries.full: As Amy and Dan vie for position as Selina's campaign manager, Ben arranges a secret lunch with a hotshot strategist. Mike tries to maintain his strict fertility schedule; Jonah is offered a job on Maddox's team; and Gary's shoulder pain threatens his job. Later, Selina is invited by Maddox to his country house, and Amy has a dinner party with the staff as part of her pitch.
